// ALM 14B r10d — hexa-native launcher SCAFFOLD (--selftest + --dry-run only).
//
// Purpose:
//   Prepare ALM 14B r10d (D8+D9 drift fix) fire path using hexa-native
//   trainer (train_alm_lora.hexa) instead of the legacy
//   `python3 /tmp/_train_alm_14b_r10d.py` pattern (banned per R37/AN13/L3-PY).
//   The existing training/launch_alm_14b_r10d.hexa is an R37 panic stub kept
//   for sweep history; this file is the replacement invocation path.
//
// Compliance:
//   R37 / AN13 / L3-PY — ZERO python3 invocations in this file. `pkill -f`
//   remains permitted as a KILL (not invoke) for residual legacy processes.
//
// Scope:
//   SCAFFOLD ONLY. live_fire() body is a placeholder that enumerates the
//   intended fire plan but DOES NOT execute remote I/O in this round. A
//   subsequent session will wire each step once the prerequisites land:
//     - hexa-lang hxqwen14b FFI Day-2 entries (forward/backward/apply)
//     - corpus_alm_70b_stripped.txt materialised + uploaded to R2
//     - Qwen2.5-14B-Instruct safetensors available at r2:anima-models/base/
//
// Plan SSOT:
//   /Users/ghost/Dev/anima/training/r10d_launch_plan.md  (§2 params, §3 aborts,
//   §8 invocation)
//
// Usage:
//   hexa training/deploy/alm_14b_r10d_hexa_native.hexa --selftest
//   hexa training/deploy/alm_14b_r10d_hexa_native.hexa \
//        --pod-id <id> --dry-run
//   LIVE_FIRE_OK=1 hexa training/deploy/alm_14b_r10d_hexa_native.hexa \
//        --pod-id <id>            # gated — will panic until live_fire() wired
//
// Differences vs CLM r4 scaffold:
//   - Trainer entry = training/train_alm_lora.hexa (LoRA r=32 α=64, q/k/v/o)
//   - Corpus = corpus_alm_70b_stripped.txt (41.8M tokens)
//   - LR schedule = warmup 200 -> peak 1e-5 -> cosine -> floor 1e-6
//   - save_every = 500 (r10c died @ step 75 w/ save_every=2000; MFS quota safe)
//   - Sentinel integration: kr_gen_sentinel.hexa deployed alongside trainer

